---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="Starting a Daycare at Home | Childcare Business Plan"
    description="Your home-based daycare opportunity depends on your state's regulations, zoning laws, and local market. Get personalized insights for your situation."
>
    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-16 px-4">
        <!-- 1. OWNERSHIP FRAMING -->
        <section class="text-center mb-16">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                YOUR Home-Based Daycare
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                Running a daycare from home offers flexibility and lower startup
                costs, but your actual opportunity depends entirely on your
                state's family childcare regulations and your local market.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 2. FACTORS THAT AFFECT OUTCOME -->
        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                What Affects Your Home Daycare
            </h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600">
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Home-based daycares operate under family childcare
                    licensing, which varies dramatically by state. Some states
                    allow you to care for up to 12 children with an assistant,
                    while others cap you at 3 without one. These capacity limits
                    directly determine your income ceiling.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Your home's zoning classification matters too. Residential
                    zoning might restrict business operations, require special
                    permits, or limit the number of non-family members allowed
                    on your property during business hours. Some neighborhoods
                    have HOA restrictions that prohibit home-based businesses
                    entirely.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Beyond regulations, your home's layout, available outdoor
                    space, and proximity to your target market all affect
                    viability. The work-life boundaries you can maintain, the
                    modifications your home requires, and the local demand for
                    home-based care create a unique business equation for every
                    provider.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. WHY GENERIC ADVICE FAILS -->
        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                Why Online Advice Often Conflicts
            </h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600">
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Search for "starting a home daycare" and you'll find wildly
                    different estimates for income potential, startup costs, and
                    viability. Some sources make it sound like easy money,
                    others paint it as barely profitable. The truth is they're
                    describing completely different regulatory and market
                    environments.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    A family daycare that thrives in one state might be
                    financially impossible in another due to capacity
                    restrictions. A profitable model in a suburban area might
                    fail in a rural community with different demographics and
                    fewer dual-income families.
                </p>
                <p>
                    You can't evaluate your opportunity using someone else's
                    numbers. Your state's regulations, your local market rates,
                    and your home's suitability create a combination that
                    requires personalized analysis, not generic guidance.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. CTA TO CALCULATOR -->
        <section class="text-center py-12 px-8 glass-panel rounded-3xl">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                See How Much YOU Could Make in Your State
            </h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Get your personalized income estimate based on your state's
                family childcare regulations.
            </p>
            <a
                href="/tools/income-builder"
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 hover:bg-teal-700 text-white font-medium px-8 py-4 shadow-lg transition-all"
            >
                Use the Free Calculator →
            </a>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>
